snippet: Mayor Cory A. Booker’s Internet start-up stalled, and it feared that his election to the Senate this fall would deprive it of its main asset: him.
abstract: Waywire, Internet start-up owned in large part by Newark Mayor Cory A Booker, is racing to find buyer; push comes with recognition that company is not making progress and amid fears that Booker's potential election to United States Senate could strip moribund venture of his presence and its main asset.

byline.original: By DAVID M. HALBFINGER and CLAIRE CAIN MILLER
byline.contributor: Raymond Hernandez and Jenna Wortham contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: Mayor Cory A. Booker’s Internet start-up stalled, and it feared that his election to the Senate this fall would deprive it of its main asset: him.

headline.main: Booker’s Web Company, Struggling, Sought Buyer as Senate Drive Began
headline.print_headline: Booker’s Web Company, Struggling, Sought Buyer as Senate Drive Began
